data.title: American Battery Technology Company CEO Ryan Melsert to present at IEA Energy Innovation Forum 2025 before G7 Energy Ministers.
data.description: American Battery Technology Company (ABTC) based in Reno, Nevada, revealed that its CEO, Ryan Melsert, participated in the IEA Energy Innovation Forum 2025 after receiving an invitation. The event was co-hosted by the International Energy Agency (IEA) and the Government of Canada on October 29, 2025, in Toronto. This forum, which served as a crucial lead-up to the G7 Energy and Environment Ministers’ Meeting on October 30, 2025, included top officials from the U.S. Department of Energy. ABTC is listed on the NASDAQ as ABAT and is recognized as an integrated critical battery materials company.

data.title: Tech futures surged on earnings winners including Amazon and Apple, despite a previous drop in stocks led by Meta. Dow Jones Futures on the rise.
data.description: Strong performances from tech giants such as Amazon and Apple led to a rise in tech futures following a slight dip in stocks led by Meta on Thursday. Dow Jones futures increased as tech stocks rebounded, with Amazon and Apple driving earnings winners. This positive momentum indicates a promising outlook for tech sector investors, despite recent fluctuations in the market.

data.title: SharkNinja transforms Love Is Blind viral 'Chicken Smoothie' moment into protein ice cream collab.
data.description: A company based in Needham, Massachusetts, SharkNinja, has capitalized on a popular scene from the Netflix show "Love Is Blind" where a contestant made a "chicken smoothie." The company has turned this viral moment into a collaboration for protein-packed ice cream. This unique partnership is expected to draw significant attention and interest from consumers.

data.title: Bitcoin rebounded to $110,000 after losing $872.33M on Thursday. Spot ETFs saw heavy outflows with $488.4M from Bitcoin funds and $184.3M from Ethereum funds. Analysts predict need to move above $112,000 for broader recovery.
data.description: Bitcoin surged back above the $110,000 mark following four consecutive days of decline which led to a total loss of $872.33 million for 218,161 traders on Thursday. Outflows were recorded in spot ETFs, with Bitcoin funds experiencing a loss of $488.4 million and Ethereum funds dropping by $184.3 million. Market analyst Ted Pillows pointed out that Bitcoin briefly dipped below $107,000 before recovering, but struggles to maintain levels above $110,000, indicating potential weakness. To initiate a broader recovery, a breakthrough above $112,000 is crucial, as failure to do so could result in a drop below $100,000. Analyst Lennaert Snyder emphasized that Bitcoin reached a low of $106,667 before bouncing back, and identified $111,300 as the next critical resistance level. More details can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: AbbVie's Q3 2025 financials: Diluted EPS $0.10 (↓88.6% GAAP) and $1.86 (↓38.0% adjusted); $1.50 impact from IPR&D expenses.
data.description: In the third quarter, the company recorded a diluted EPS of $0.10 on a GAAP basis, marking a significant decline of 88.6%. Adjusted diluted EPS stood at $1.86, showing a 38.0% decrease. These figures incorporate a negative impact of $1.50 per share due to acquired IPR&D and milestones expense. Overall, the company reported a decrease in net income for the third quarter.

data.title: Novo Tellus partners with Grand Venture Technology for global growth; Aalberts completes privatization, progressing global influence.
data.description: Singapore-based Grand Venture Technology is set for enhanced global expansion following the completion of its privatization by Aalberts. The development took place on October 31, 2025. Novo Tellus, a prominent private equity fund specializing in the development of industrial and technology firms, released a statement expressing their satisfaction with the move. The deal signifies a significant milestone for Grand Venture Technology as it gears up for future growth opportunities on an international scale.

data.title: AV and OpenJAUS partner to enhance Autonomous Uncrewed System interoperability, benefiting industry and defense sectors.
data.description: A collaboration has been announced between AV and OpenJAUS in Arlington, Virginia. This collaboration aims to enhance interoperability for Autonomous Uncrewed System (UxS). The partnership is expected to benefit both parties, as well as advance the technology in the field. This initiative underscores the growing importance of autonomous systems in various industries. It is a significant step towards achieving seamless integration and cooperation among UxS, ultimately contributing to improved efficiency and effectiveness. Stay tuned for further updates as this collaboration progresses.

data.title: Equifax (NYSE: EFX) CEOs to attend 2 investor conferences in November including J.P. Morgan Ultimate Services Investor Conference.
data.description: Atlanta, on October 31, 2025, Equifax® (NYSE: EFX) announced its participation in two investor conferences scheduled for November. The company's CEO, Mark Begor, and CFO, John Gamble, will take part in the J.P. Morgan Ultimate Services Investor Conference. The purpose of their participation is to provide insights about the company's performance and future prospects to investors. This move indicates Equifax's proactive approach towards investor engagement and transparency.
